# SCSS Modules

## File Naming

`ComponentName.module.scss` — colocated with `index.tsx`.

## Class Naming

Use camelCase for class names (required for JS import).

```scss
// ❌ Bad
.header-content { ... }
.Header_Content { ... }

// ✅ Good
.headerContent { ... }
.wrapper { ... }
```

## Nesting

Max 3 levels deep. Flatten with BEM-like naming when deeper.

```scss
// ❌ Bad: too deep
.card {
  .header {
    .title {
      .icon { ... }
    }
  }
}

// ✅ Good
.card { ... }
.cardHeader { ... }
.cardTitle { ... }
.cardIcon { ... }
```

## Responsive

- Mobile-first approach
- Use variables or mixins for breakpoints — keep them consistent
- Avoid hardcoded pixel values for breakpoints

## Variables

- Use SCSS variables for colors, spacing, fonts in shared files (`src/styles/`)
- Use CSS custom properties when runtime theming is needed

## No Utility Classes

This project uses SCSS Modules, not Tailwind. Don't add inline utility classes to JSX.
